canonical:
  title: 上大宋皇帝謝賜曆日表
  author: 郭元
  language: lzh
  text: 具官臣某言去天禧四年四月日入朝使崔元信回奉傳詔書一道伏蒙聖恩賜臣天禧四年乾元具註曆一卷者文思之化丕冒海隅曆象爰頒別爲時訓伏惟皇帝陛下與乾坤同載使品物流亨念辰卞之小邦本依正朔擧羲和之舊職克授寅賓豈料孱微叨玆注矚臣敢不示農桑之早晚用彰天子之所知稼穡之艱難永慰小人之勞力况自發函之後開卷已來窺御曆之無窮率群臣而共抃
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 上大宋皇帝謝賜曆日表
  author: 郭元
  language: lzh
  text: 具官臣某言。去天禧四年四月日。入朝使崔元信回。奉傳詔書一道。伏蒙聖恩。賜臣天禧四年乾元具註曆一卷者。文思之化。丕冒海隅。曆象爰頒。別爲時訓。伏惟皇帝陛下。與乾坤同載。使品物流亨。念辰卞之小邦。本依正朔。擧羲和之舊職。克授寅賓。豈料孱微叨玆注矚。臣敢不示農桑之早晚。用彰天子之所知稼穡之艱難。永慰小人之勞力。况自發函之後。開卷已來。窺御曆之無窮。率群臣而共抃。
korean:
  title: 대송황제께 책력을 하사함을 사례하는 표
  author: 곽원
  language: kor
  text: 구관(具官) 신 모는 아뢰옵나이다.지난 천희(天禧) 4년 4월 일에 입조사(入朝使) 최원(崔元)이 돌아와 전하는 조서(詔書) 한 통을 받들어 보니, 성상께서 신에게 천희 4년 건원구주력(乾元具註曆) 한 권을 하사하심이었나이다.문사(文思)하신 교화가 크게 해우(海隅)에까지 미쳐 역상(曆象)을 이에 나누어주시어 특별히 세시(歲時)의 가르침으로 삼으셨나이다.엎드려 생각건대, 황제폐하께서 건곤(乾坤)과 더불어 함께 실으시고[載] 만물로 하여금 형통하게 하시면서 진변(辰卞)의 작은 나라가 본래 정삭(正朔)을 의지하는 것을 생각하사, 희화(羲和 역관(曆官))의 구직(舊職)을 거행케 하여 인빈(寅賓)을 주시니, 뜻밖에 하찮은 작은 나라가 외람되이 이러한 권주(眷住)를 받은지라, 신이 감히 이로써 농상(農桑)의 조만(早晩)을 보이어 천자(天子)의 □하신 바를 나타내고 가색(稼穡)의 어려움을 알아 길이 백성들의 노역(勞役)을 위로하지 않으오리이까. 하물며 함(函)을 열고 책을 펴보니, 어력(御曆)의 무궁하심을 엿보았는지라, 군신(群臣)을 거느리고 함께 춤추나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0360_010_0260&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Memorial of Gratitude to the Great Song Emperor for the Gift of the Calendar
  author: Gwak Won
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Your servant humbly presents this memorial.

    In the fourth month of the fourth year of Tianxi, when the emissary Choe Won returned from court bearing an imperial edict, I received with gratitude the gracious gift of Your Majesty: one volume of the Tianxi fourth year Qianyuan Annotated Calendar.

    The transformative wisdom of the Son of Heaven extends its great influence even to the distant margins of the sea. The celestial patterns are thereby distributed, appointed as the teachings of the seasons for all times. Your Majesty stands in unity with Heaven and Earth itself, causing all creatures to flourish and prosper. Mindful of this small domain at the edge of the world, which has always depended upon the correct calendar reckoning, you have revived the ancient office of the celestial officials, granting us the privilege to welcome the seasons with proper ceremony.

    Who could have imagined that this insignificant and remote kingdom would receive such remarkable attention? Your servant dare not fail to reveal the proper times for farming and sericulture, thereby manifesting the wisdom that only the Son of Heaven possesses, and making clear the difficulties of agriculture—thus bringing lasting comfort to the labors of the common people. Indeed, since opening the imperial packet and unfolding these pages, I have glimpsed the boundless perfection of the imperial calendar, and together with all the officials, we dance in celebration.
  footnotes:
    - Tianxi (天禧) was a reign period of the Northern Song emperor Zhenzong (真宗), spanning 1016-1021 CE.
    - The Qianyuan calendar (乾元具註曆) was an important astronomical and agricultural reference text distributed by the Song court to tributary states.
    - The reference to 'welcoming the seasons' (寅賓) echoes the ancient Chinese ritual practice of receiving the seasons with proper ceremony, establishing a kingdom's legitimacy through adherence to the cosmic order.
    - The 'ancient office of the celestial officials' alludes to Xi and He (羲和), legendary sage-officials who regulated the calendar in antiquity.
